# ============================================================
# .env file for the Forest Fire Prediction backend
# ============================================================
#
# This file controls runtime configuration that you don't want
# baked into the source code. The only setting at the moment is
# the HTTP Basic auth password.
#
# To enable password protection on the deployed server:
#   1. Set APP_PASSWORD below to your chosen password
#   2. Restart the server (the file is read once at startup)
#
# To disable password protection (useful for local development):
#   1. Comment out the APP_PASSWORD line below (add a # in front)
#   2. Restart the server
#
# The password is shared across all users. When set, anyone who
# loads the app in their browser gets a native popup asking for
# any username (it's ignored) and the password. The browser
# remembers the credentials for the rest of the session.
#
# This is a single-shared-password gate, not a user account
# system. If you need to revoke access for one person, change
# the password here and redistribute to the rest.
#
# DO NOT commit this file to git with a real password in it.
# It is listed in .gitignore for that reason.

APP_PASSWORD=change-me-to-something-real
